{
  "doc_id": "33643",
  "text": "Althought some PC paraquat degradation works have been reported [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] , in the present work, PEC degradation of paraquat was investigated for the first time. Highly active nanotube structured TiO 2 on Ti layers as photoanodes was prepared by anodic oxidation method in EG medium and used in paraquat degradation. The effects of anodic oxidation time on nanotube length and the amount of Pt loading by cyclic voltammetry were also investigated. Photoanodes prepared by thermal oxidation (Ti/TiO 2 -500) [CITATION_4] and anodic oxidation in HF medium (Ti/TiO 2 -NTHF-X) [CITATION_5] were used for comparison.",
